rComments: Reasoning and critical think. The easiness of his tests was completely undone by the unclearness of the questions. His english grammar is very poor. You will be left guessing between what's written down, what you think it means, and what you think he thinks it means. He does have a sense of humor and is nice. But as a professor I would stongly recommend that you avoid him. He does not even show up to his exams, including the final!

Yes, it is often hard to understand what he is saying through his accent but he provides lots of examples to help clarify and tries to engage the class in them. He does have the worst technical skills and it is often hard to hear him because not only is he foreign but he is a low-talker. A very nice guy tho, very approachable if need be. I wouldn't recommend taking any courses with him though.

Yes, he is a sweetheart. And his accent is not really that bad. And the tests are extremely easy. But good christ, he is so boring! Class is tedious, he speaks torturously slowly, I did not learn a thing. It should be called "Greek Philosophers" instead of "Great Philosophers", because that's all you will ever do.
It's not that he's a bad guy, it's just the strong accent that takes away from the message he's trying to convey. I personally found the class very boring.
He is not a very clear professor. He only uses examples to explain concepts. Also, his English is really awful. He should not be teaching a class that relies heavily on language use.
Amazing Prof. one of the best in philosphy department

He is a great prof. Tests refelct lectures 100%, lectures crystal clear and straight forward no extra b.s and rambling he's just to the point and that's it, what we need to learn for the exam is what he tells us nothing more and nothing less, exam review is a exactly what is on the exam, Dr. Jankovic is also very smart.. funny when hes nervous

Proffesor Jankovic is very helpful. OMG this guy knows his philsophy like no tomorow ... he's actually a replica of SOCARTES like it's remarkable the fact that he knows that much philsophy ...one draw back for his course is he has a HUGEE accent but that doesn't matter his knowledge and method of teaching canels that out
Very kind and helpful.... accent is huge but his knowledge of the stuff is amazing better than socartes

Dr. Jankovic is a very intellectual and smart. He is propbably the one proph that knows every inch of philosphy there is possible, people just need to tune in a bit more as he is almost impossible to understand and its so funny when he gets excited or nervous which is always lol Dr. Jankovic is the man

I'll admit his accent makes understanding a little difficult but eventually you will get used to it. Unfortunately most people do not take this course out of interest, they take it because they have to. Although he tries to inspire interest he has to beg students to participate. He becomes very exited(and better) when people answer and participate.

People should quit complaining about his accent. You could understand what he was saying and his classes were quite fun. The exams were really easy since he basically went over what was going to be in them during class. He takes most of his examples from the book, so if you skip class you just have to read a few pages and you're fine.

He was a nice guy... but every form of communication he used was hard to understand... his strong accent and poor english made it impossible to understand his lectures. Also, he provided no notes besides his scribbly, unreadable writing on the board.

Very difficult to understand this professor as he gives lectures, and he struggles to understand you as well.  He is a friendly person; however, I would highly recommend saving yourself stress and switching into another course.

He is hard to understand, not only because he has an accent but because he gets nervous and stumbles on his words. But if you can get past that he really isnt a bad teacher. He always tries so hard and his tests are exactly what he went over in class. And he gets so excited when people laugh at his jokes that i cant help liking him.

He's really hard to understand sometimes, especially at first i couldn't understand ANYTHING but eventually it gets better. I hated him at first and now he's not so bad. His tests are EASY and he can funny, make sure to study examples given in class.
Hard to understand, no doubt there. But if you're ok with accents you shouldn't have any problem. Extremely easy course, and he's very willing to help if you need it.

Yes, he has an accent, but please, have a little decency and let the guy teach. Of course there are spelling errors...a tad annoying...he does however, cover material quickly and with no set definition for anything, you'd think it changes every time...Overall I thought class was entertaining because, he joked about his lack of technical abilities..

Notwithstanding the previous comments, I have to admit that this professor is, indeed, a fine one. He tries to create a safe learning environment, assesses students’ prior knowledge, and engages the class. I went to all the lectures and I loved it. Students need to pay more attention to the purpose of the class, rather than to other trivial matters

VERY hard to understand. I sat there through some of the classes and I could not understand a single word he was saying. Thick accent and spoke too softly. On top of that, his microphone was creating so much static and thats all you would here. Decided to drop the course. Followed the textbook closely. Nice guy though.

Did not like his class.  I'm not sure if it was a combination of his thick accent, his teaching style, or his lack of guide whatsoever.  He would just ramble on the whole class, and that's it.  He hardly slowed down and there were hardly any notes on the board.  There was no level of interest.  He was a nice guy, though.

People on here seriously need to get a grip. I can't believe some of the comments on here! Its called an ACCENT people. Get over it. It wasn't even that bad. There is a world outside of North America. Anyway, a decent professor. If you e-mail him he responds quickly. Evaluations are pretty fair. I would take his class again.
Spell Check.

thick, thick accent!!! I feel bad for the guy, everyone was so mean to him. I probably went to  8 lectures out of the whole term and I did well on all my examinations. EASYYYY if you go over the problems in the book. All he does in class is use examples from the book, therefore going to class is POINTLESS.

His midterms were fine and are worth less than midterms for other classes. If you read the textbook you can answer the problems easily. Sit near the front, be quiet and read the textbook!! He was a fine professor!!

If you can avoid this professor, DO IT!!! I don't want to be mean but he is literally hard to sit there and listen to.  It's painful.  You spend more effort tryin to figure out what the hell he's saying rather than the work.  I dropped the class and I'm going to take it with another professor because Jankovic's tests are hard and worth ALOT!

No English; not responsive to students; takes 3-4 classes to go over 1 chapter; shines the overhead projector on the class everyday instead of the blackboard.
